wherigo_decompile_message:
Unfortunately, the GC Wizard cannot extract the LUA code offline at the moment. If you like, the cartridge (and nothing else!) will be send to our server for analysis.

Alternatively you can put manually decompiled LUA code directly into the tool from a file or an internet resource.

Meanwhile we are searching for an offline solution.

For getting the LUA-Sourcecode you should save it to file.

To extract the LUA-Sourcecode you need Java and also unluac.jar from sourceforge.net
https://sourceforge.net/projects/unluac/files/latest/download

Usage:
java -jar unluac.jar myfile.lua > myfile_decompiled.lua
